James Neill https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_Neill 0 James Neill (September 29, 1860 – March 16, 1931) was an American stage actor and film actor of the silent era. He appeared in 113 films between 1913 and 1930. His wife, and frequent costar on stage and screen, was Edythe Chapman. In 1902 the couple starred on Broadway in the play The Red Knight. Upon his death on March 16, 1931, he was buried in Bonaventure Cemetery, Savannah, Georgia.
